The core of the library is located in the 'Lib' folder, the external modules are located in subfolders of the 'Mod' folder (one subfolder per module). The '*.py' files in this directory are example programs to test the library. 

When the current directory is the working directory:

	- command to build the library

		make lib

	- command to build the external modules

		make mods

You are now ready to use PyTreeLib!
